articles.title: Far-right candidate takes shock lead in Romania presidential election - BBC.com
articles.description: Calin Georgescu, a critic of the EU and Nato, looks set to face the pro-Europe prime minister in the second round.
articles.content:
A far-right, pro-Russia candidate has taken a surprise lead in the first round of Romania's presidential election, with preliminary results putting his pro-Europe rival in close second.
